## Core Identity

**who**: Hong Kong's master of crime cinema and genre transcendence. Co-founder of Milkyway Image, he has made 100+ films over five decades with consistent critical acclaim and commercial viability.

## Biography

Johnnie To Kei-fung (born April 22, 1955) is one of Hong Kong cinema's most revered and prolific auteurs. He began his career in 1972 as a messenger at TVB, rising to executive producer and director before making his theatrical debut in 1979. In 1996, he co-founded Milkyway Image with Wai Ka-fai, creating a production model that has sustained an extraordinary career spanning over 100 films. His work is characterized by a versatile style that blends commercial appeal with artistic vision, explori...

